e, the nodule is on the back of the hand, which isn't typically a high-sunlight area.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043369,0.074755,0.084829,0.092806,0.09753,0.097884,0.10068,0.096635,0.092329,0.083365,0.073924,0.061893],"unified_progress":[0.041827,0.074271,0.088601,0.098197,0.1038,0.10157,0.099609,0.096333,0.094478,0.082764,0.066986,0.051569]},{"section":10,"text":"That makes me think there might be an underlying condition that predisposes her to skin cancer.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043184,0.087135,0.097548,0.11239,0.09587,0.092018,0.090362,0.087514,0.082448,0.078634,0.070209,0.062685],"unified_progress":[0.035932,0.068008,0.084547,0.096039,0.09782,0.099032,0.1015,0.098879,0.093779,0.089838,0.075956,0.058667]},{"section":11,"text":"The key here is the germline mutation in a nucleotide excision repair enzyme.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038114,0.063986,0.079846,0.088771,0.097459,0.098981,0.098636,0.096261,0.091832,0.090455,0.080772,0.074888],"unified_progress":[0.037269,0.067405,0.082784,0.094474,0.097881,0.098675,0.098575,0.095089,0.092613,0.087396,0.078622,0.069216]},{"section":12,"text":"Nucleotide excision repair (NER) is a process that fixes damaged DNA, like from UV light.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041072,0.061861,0.077054,0.088345,0.097133,0.1005,0.10407,0.10269,0.096971,0.08917,0.076448,0.064688],"unified_progress":[0.040381,0.068678,0.086428,0.096757,0.10182,0.10638,0.10294,0.097468,0.092242,0.084433,0.069686,0.05279]},{"section":13,"text":"If there's a mutation in this repair mechanism, the body can't fix DNA damage effectively, leading to more mutations and a higher risk of cancer.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.05546,0.063658,0.074837,0.084054,0.091196,0.095063,0.099062,0.099324,0.097148,0.090504,0.08063,0.069063],"unified_progress":[0.04229,0.064307,0.080444,0.08965,0.09674,0.10277,0.10116,0.099026,0.095559,0.090058,0.077652,0.060342]},{"section":14,"text":"I remember that there are several genetic disorders related to defective DNA repair.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035647,0.058983,0.075749,0.083721,0.093632,0.097477,0.097715,0.09936,0.095151,0.1024,0.085466,0.074697],"unified_progress":[0.038509,0.069067,0.082815,0.095802,0.097378,0.098241,0.099332,0.096545,0.092244,0.093173,0.077104,0.059791]},{"section":15,"text":"One of them is xeroderma pigmentosum (XP), which is characterized by extreme sensitivity to UV light.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028826,0.054407,0.070649,0.082447,0.094812,0.10097,0.11093,0.11205,0.10492,0.095565,0.079796,0.064618],"unified_progress":[0.030508,0.059113,0.081838,0.094079,0.1024,0.11424,0.10715,0.10351,0.096462,0.0889,0.069037,0.052773]},{"section":16,"text":"People with XP have a high risk of developing skin cancers, including SCC and basal cell carcinoma, especially in sun-exposed areas.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041097,0.059391,0.06933,0.07824,0.08964,0.095972,0.10481,0.10729,0.10357,0.094901,0.084184,0.071567],"unified_progress":[0.040335,0.063139,0.078803,0.090378,0.096548,0.10508,0.10268,0.10136,0.096494,0.090177,0.075086,0.05993]},{"section":17,"text":"They also have hypopigmentation because the skin doesn't tan and the repair mechanism is faulty.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039618,0.05794,0.072132,0.081634,0.092837,0.098247,0.10376,0.10453,0.10296,0.093933,0.083661,0.068748],"unified_progress":[0.042608,0.068176,0.084381,0.093214,0.10012,0.10284,0.10098,0.098489,0.095706,0.087463,0.072008,0.054019]},{"section":18,"text":"Another possibility is something like Cockayne syndrome, but that's more associated with neurological issues and doesn't typically present with skin cancer as prominently.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028801,0.052287,0.06729,0.078084,0.08972,0.0966,0.10594,0.10947,0.10777,0.10208,0.089197,0.07276],"unified_progress":[0.03075,0.057951,0.078034,0.089439,0.096869,0.1071,0.10407,0.1039,0.099319,0.097206,0.078281,0.05708]},{"section":19,"text":"There's also trichothiodystrophy, but that's rarer and often presents with other symptoms like hair and nail problems.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027002,0.050373,0.065791,0.077475,0.090917,0.098418,0.10995,0.1135,0.10957,0.10063,0.08678,0.069595],"unified_progress":[0.029593,0.057559,0.078293,0.091852,0.09941,0.10897,0.10756,0.10645,0.10081,0.095709,0.07375,0.050051]},{"section":20,"text":"Given the age of the patient and the skin manifestations, XP seems the most likely.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03745,0.054914,0.065142,0.07077,0.078237,0.082445,0.085704,0.090359,0.092521,0.10923,0.10996,0.12326],"unified_progress":[0.035106,0.056469,0.066342,0.076369,0.081103,0.087473,0.08868,0.093965,0.094653,0.098458,0.10593,0.11545]},{"section":21,"text":"The hypopigmented patches could be areas where the skin hasn't been able to tan due to the inability to repair UV damage, leading to depigmentation.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038107,0.053659,0.067864,0.077837,0.088362,0.094475,0.10103,0.10338,0.10465,0.099617,0.091711,0.079305],"unified_progress":[0.036242,0.060133,0.076215,0.087351,0.094192,0.098666,0.099108,0.099968,0.10045,0.095879,0.084223,0.067577]},{"section":22,"text":"The ulcers and crusts might be from repeated damage and infections in those areas.","dimension":12,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03618,0.05366,0.068638,0.078708,0.089784,0.096389,0.10296,0.10545,0.10554,0.098287,0.089613,0.074785],"unified_progress":[0.04085,0.065653,0.078728,0.087268,0.094399,0.1002,0.099702,0.10059,0.09855,0.094556,0.07953,0.059968]},{"section":23,"text":"The SCC on the ba